{
  "texts": [
    "For ML prediction, Wang et al.",
    "83 developed an artificial intelligence platform that employs the crystal structure and some experimental descriptors to build ML models, thus can successfully predict and screen the superionic conductors with high diffusion coefficients and ionic conductivity.",
    "For ML analysis, Zhang et al.",
    "10 demonstrate an efficient utilization of unsupervisedbased ML analysis for screening fast Li-ion conductors by correlating the new crystal structure with the ionic conductivity of the electrolytes; meanwhile unrevealing the fundamental rules for the understanding of the key parameters to influence multi-dimensional properties, for example, the ionic conductivity and the stability.",
    "For ML inverse learning, ML plays a critical role in optimizing the fabrication of solid-state electrolyte films through reverse engineering."
  ]
}